post_text:
Please join us in welcoming Heather Parsons to the Gem Prep Team!

Heather Parsons serves as the Principal Supervisor for Gem Prep Schools. She is focused on providing principals with the coaching and support necessary for effective school leadership.

Prior to joining the Gem community, Mrs. Parsons served as the Director of Curriculum and Instruction for Navigator Schools in Gilroy, Hollister, and Watsonville, California. She was instrumental in helping the schools rank number one in the Silicon Valley for closing the achievement gap for English learners and socioeconomically disadvantaged students.

Mrs. Parsons holds a Master of Science in Instructional Design & Technology from Walden University and a Bachelor's in Communication from San Francisco State University.

post_text: Gem Prep Online scholars are fortunate that the recent COVID-19 prevention measures do not affect our daily learning. Still, many of us are adapting to a new lifestyle, one that involves staying active and busy at home. Here are a few ideas to help fill those extra curricular openings you may now have. YouTube and Facebook are wonderful resources for how-to videos, free lessons, and even the occasional concert by some headlining artists. Keep checking back, as I will add resources to the comments as I run across them. Stay healthy!
